event: message_saved
data: {"messageId":"LEJTgJN0yBBwu_rFfFaz7","role":"user","content":"Design and prototype a complex multi-agent system for automated security incident response. Execute ALL steps:\n\n1. Use list_agent_templates to see available agent templates\n\n2. Use get_framework_status to check which agentic frameworks are available\n\n3. Use list_available_tools to see what MCP tools could be assigned to agents\n\n4. Use design_custom_agent to design a 'SecurityTriageAgent' with these specs:\n   - Role: Triage incoming security alerts from multiple sources\n   - Tools: loki_search_errors, prometheus_alerts, k8s_get_events, incident_create\n   - Decision logic: Classify severity (P1-P4) based on alert type and scope\n\n5. Use design_custom_agent to design a 'ForensicsAgent' with these specs:\n   - Role: Deep investigation of confirmed incidents\n   - Tools: admin_system_postgres_raw_query, loki_query, k8s_get_pod_logs, web_search\n   - Decision logic: Correlate events across data sources to find root cause\n\n6. Use design_custom_agent to design an 'RemediationAgent' with these specs:\n   - Role: Execute automated remediation based on runbooks\n   - Tools: runbook_execute, k8s_restart_deployment, k8s_scale_deployment, incident_resolve\n   - Decision logic: Match incident type to runbook, execute with human approval for P1\n\n7. Use suggest_tools_for_task with task 'automated security incident response pipeline'\n\n8. Use search_tool_documentation to find docs for the incident management tools\n\nPresent the complete multi-agent architecture as:\n- Agent graph (which agent calls which)\n- Tool assignments per agent\n- Escalation and handoff logic\n- Estimated execution flow for a sample P2 incident","timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:08:39.161Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

