event: tool_executing
data: {"name":"design_custom_agent","arguments":{"description":"Design a 'SecurityTriageAgent' that triages incoming security alerts from multiple sources (Prometheus, Loki, Kubernetes events, external feeds). The agent should:\n1. Continuously monitor alert streams from Prometheus and Loki error logs\n2. Classify each alert by severity (P1-Critical, P2-Major, P3-Minor, P4-Low) based on alert type, blast radius, affected services, and whether it involves data exposure\n3. Deduplicate alerts and correlate related alerts into a single incident\n4. Create incidents automatically with proper severity classification\n5. Route P1 incidents immediately to the ForensicsAgent and notify on-call\n6. Route P2-P3 incidents to ForensicsAgent with normal priority\n7. Auto-close P4 incidents that match known false-positive patterns\nDecision logic: If alert involves data exposure or auth bypass -> P1. If service outage affecting >50% users -> P1. If single service degradation -> P2. If non-prod or limited scope -> P3. If informational/known pattern -> P4.","framework":"langgraph","tools":"loki_search_errors, prometheus_alerts, incident_create, incident_list, incident_escalate"},"toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_018hicM5Xcvzs1aAw3asF4fj","targetServer":"openagentic_agent_architect","timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:09:04.851Z"}

