ch alert by severity (P1-Critical, P2-Major, P3-Minor, P4-Low) based on alert type, blast radius, affected services, and whether it involves data exposure\n3. Deduplicate alerts and correlate related alerts into a single incident\n4. Create incidents automatically with proper severity classification\n5. Route P1 incidents immediately to the ForensicsAgent and notify on-call\n6. Route P2-P3 incidents to ForensicsAgent with normal priority\n7. Auto-close P4 incidents that match known false-positive patterns\nDecision logic: If alert involves data exposure or auth bypass -> P1. If service outage affecting >50% users -> P1. If single service degradation -> P2. If non-prod or limited scope -> P3. If informational/known pattern -> P4.","framework":"langgraph","tools":"loki_search_errors, prometheus_alerts, incident_create, incident_list, incident_escalate"},"result":null,"error":"connect ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080","status":"failed","startTime":1771625343809,"endTime":1771625345386,"duration":1577,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:09:05.386Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_016BwudfAsqihAyW8CazyD4t","name":"design_custom_agent","tool":"design_custom_agent","toolName":"design_custom_agent","serverId":"openagentic_agent_architect","serverName":"openagentic_agent_architect","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"description":"Design a 'ForensicsAgent' that performs deep investigation of confirmed security incidents. The agent should:\n1. Receive incident handoffs from the SecurityTriageAgent with initial classification\n2. Search error logs across all namespaces and time windows using Loki\n3. Correlate events across multiple data sources (logs, metrics, Kubernetes events)\n4. Search the web for known CVEs, attack patterns, or similar incidents\n5. Build a timeline of events leading up to the incident\n6. Identify the root cause and blast radius (affected services, users, data)\n7. Determine if the incident is an active attack, misconfiguration, or system failure\n8. Hand off findings to the RemediationAgent with a structured investigation report\nDecision logic: Start with the alerting service logs -> expand to dependent services -> check for lateral movement -> correlate with external threat intelligence -> classify as attack/misconfig/failure -> estimate blast radius -> generate investigation report.","framework":"langgraph","tools":"loki_search_errors, web_search, incident_get, incident_update_status, k8s_list_deployments, k8s_get_deployment, k8s_cluster_health"},"result":null,"error":"connect ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080","status":"failed","startTime":1771625343809,"endTime":1771625345386,"duration":1577,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:09:05.386Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01DXxSwvzANYBhePyT7ox8fM","name":"design_custom_agent","tool":"design_custom_agent","toolName":"design_custom_agent","serverId":"openagentic_agent_architect","serverName":"openagentic_agent_architect","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"description":"Design a 'RemediationAgent' that executes automated remediation based on runbooks for security incidents. The agent should:\n1. Receive investigation reports from the ForensicsAgent with root cause and recommended actions\n2. Match the incident type and root cause to predefined runbooks (pod restart, scale up, network isolation, credential rotation, rollback)\n3. For P1 incidents: Request human approval before executing any remediation action\n4. For P2-P3 incidents: Execute remediation automatically but log all actions\n5. For P4 incidents: Auto-remediate silently\n6. Execute remediation steps: restart deployments, scale deployments, execute runbooks\n7. Verify remediation success by checking service health post-action\n8. Resolve the incident with documentation of all actions taken\n9. If remediation fails, escalate the incident and notify the on-call team\nDecision logic: Match incident_type to runbook -> check severity for approval gate -> execute remediation steps sequentially -> verify health -> if healthy resolve incident -> if not healthy retry once -> if still failing escalate to human.","framework":"langgraph","tools":"k8s_restart_deployment, k8s_scale_deployment, k8s_cluster_health, incident_resolve, incident_escalate, incident_link_runbook, incident_update_status"},"result":null,"error":"connect ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080","status":"failed","startTime":1771625343809,"endTime":1771625345386,"duration":1577,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:09:05.386Z"}],"tokenUsage":{"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":106,"total_tokens":106},"model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","source":"database","confirmed":true,"final":true}

